msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (_pācittiya_)"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:0.4"
msgid "Bhojanavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 37"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:0.5"
msgid "37. Vikālabhojanasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on eating at the wrong time"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-cs-bu-pc37.1, pts-vp-en.2.335, ms2V_800
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena rājagahe giraggasamajjo hoti."
msgstr "At that time in Rājagaha there was a hilltop festival,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.3"
msgid "Sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū giraggasamajjaṃ dassanāya agamaṃsu."
msgstr "and the monks from the group of seventeen went to see it."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.4"
msgid "Manussā sattarasavaggiye bhikkhū passitvā nahāpetvā vilimpetvā bhojetvā khādanīyaṃ adaṃsu."
msgstr "When people saw the monks, they bathed them, anointed them, fed them staples, and gave them non-staple food."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.5"
msgid "Sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū khādanīyaṃ ādāya ārāmaṃ gantvā chabbaggiye bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "The monks brought that food back to the monastery. And they said to the monks from the group of six,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.6"
msgid "“gaṇhāthāvuso, khādanīyaṃ khādathā”ti."
msgstr "“Take food and eat it!”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.7"
msgid "“Kuto tumhehi, āvuso, khādanīyaṃ laddhan”ti?"
msgstr "“But where did you get this food?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.8"
msgid "Sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "And they told them."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.9"
msgid "“Kiṃ pana tumhe, āvuso, vikāle bhojanaṃ bhuñjathā”ti?"
msgstr "“So are you eating at the wrong time?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.10"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti."
msgstr "“Yes.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.11"
msgid "Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "The monks from the group of six complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.12"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū vikāle bhojanaṃ bhuñjissantī”ti."
msgstr "“How can those monks from the group of seventeen eat at the wrong time?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms2V_801, pts-vp-en.2.336
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.13"
msgid "Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They told the monks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.14"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.15"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.16"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū vikāle bhojanaṃ bhuñjissantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can those monks from the group of seventeen eat at the wrong time?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.17"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, vikāle bhojanaṃ bhuñjathā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.18"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.19"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.20"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, vikāle bhojanaṃ bhuñjissatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you eat at the wrong time?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.21"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.22"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.22a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc3, ms2V_802
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:1.23"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu vikāle khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādeyya vā bhuñjeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk eats staple or non-staple food at the wrong time, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc4, pts-vp-pli4.86, pts-cs-bu-pc37.2.1, ms2V_803
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc5, ms2V_804
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.1.6"
msgid "Vikālo nāma"
msgstr "At the wrong time:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.1.7"
msgid "majjhanhike vītivatte yāva aruṇuggamanā."
msgstr "when the middle of the day has passed, until dawn."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc6, pts-vp-en.2.337, ms2V_805
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.1.8"
msgid "Khādanīyaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Non-staple food:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.1.9"
msgid "pañca bhojanāni—yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ ṭhapetvā avasesaṃ khādanīyaṃ nāma."
msgstr "apart from the five staple foods, the post-midday tonics, the seven-day tonics, and the lifetime tonics—the rest is called “non-staple food.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, ms2V_806
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.1.10"
msgid "Bhojanīyaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Staple food:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.1.11"
msgid "pañca bhojanāni—"
msgstr "there are five kinds of staple food:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.1.12"
msgid "odano, kummāso, sattu, maccho, maṃsaṃ."
msgstr "cooked grain, porridge, flour, fish, and meat."

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc8, ms2V_807
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.1.13"
msgid "“Khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he receives staple or non-staple food with the intention of eating it, he commits and offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.1.14"
msgid "Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc9, pts-cs-bu-pc37.2.2, ms2V_808
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.2.1"
msgid "Vikāle vikālasaññī khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is the wrong time, and he perceives it as the wrong time, and he eats staple or non-staple food, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.2.2"
msgid "Vikāle vematiko khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is the wrong time, but he is unsure if it is, and he eats staple or non-staple food, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.2.3"
msgid "Vikāle kālasaññī khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is the wrong time, but he perceives it as the right time, and he eats staple or non-staple food, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10, ms2V_809
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.2.4"
msgid "Yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ āhāratthāya paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he receives post-midday tonics, seven-day tonics, or lifetime tonics for the purpose of food, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.2.5"
msgid "Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "For every mouthful, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.2.6"
msgid "Kāle vikālasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is the right time, but he perceives it as the wrong time, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.2.7"
msgid "Kāle vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is the right time, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.2.8"
msgid "Kāle kālasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is the right time, and he perceives it as the right time, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc11, pts-cs-bu-pc37.2.3, ms2V_810
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.3.2"
msgid "yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ sati paccaye paribhuñjati,  "
msgstr "if, when there is a reason, he uses post-midday tonics, seven-day tonics, or lifetime tonics;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.3.3"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.3.4"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc12, ms2V_811
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc37:2.3.5"
msgid "Vikālabhojanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ."
msgstr "The seventh rule, the training rule on eating at the wrong time, is finished."
